data.name: Privilege
desc: defines a list of flags (bitmaps) which determines the access rights of a user or a user group.
This list may grow in the future.

items.name: SELECT
lines: indicates that a user is allowed to read the data.

items.name: INSERT
lines: indicates that a user is allowed to insert new data.

items.name: UPDATE
lines: indicates that a user is allowed to update data.

items.name: DELETE
lines: indicates that a user is allowed to delete data.

items.name: READ
lines: indicates that a user is allowed to read the structure of a definition object.

items.name: CREATE
lines: indicates that a user is allowed to create a definition object.

items.name: ALTER
lines: indicates that a user is allowed to alter an existing object.

items.name: REFERENCE
lines: indicates that a user is allowed to set foreign keys for a table.

items.name: DROP
lines: indicates that a user is allowed to drop a definition object.
